address = {New York, NY, USA},
url = {https://doi.org/10.1145/3664968.3665011},
doi = {10.1145/3664968.3665011},
abstract = {The effective and dependable operation of water production facilities stands as a cornerstone in safeguarding the accessibility of potable water in regionally significant areas such as RMUTR. These facilities assume a pivotal role in the treatment and distribution of water to meet the demands of local communities, thereby underscoring their indispensable importance for public health in this place. Consequently, the implementation of robust management strategies, technological advancements, and stringent maintenance protocols becomes imperative to uphold the uninterrupted provision of clean water to communities reliant on these facilities. This study is focused on enhancing the efficiency and reliability of water production facilities, specifically within the context of specific significant areas like RMUTR. The study introduces the development of an Overall Equipment Effectiveness (OEE) system tailored for continuous monitoring of machinery health within these facilities. Functioning as a virtual representation of physical assets, this OEE system facilitates real-time analysis, predictive maintenance, and performance optimization. Such an approach embodies proactive plant management, striving to ensure the sustained availability of clean water, which is pivotal for community welfare. The proposed system integrates cutting-edge sensor technologies, data analytics, and machine learning algorithms to monitor the condition of critical machinery components such as pumps, valves, and motors. By harnessing real-time data from these components, the OEE system offers insights into operational status and preempts potential issues before they escalate, by continuously monitoring machinery health and performance, the OEE system contributes significantly to proactive maintenance practices, thereby minimizing downtime and maximizing productivity in water production operations.},
